                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410405-1260-offence-1 t18410405-cd-225"></join>1st of December</rs>, 27 1/2 yards of printed cotton, value 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1 looking-glass and stand, value 20<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18410405-name-1414" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1414" type="surname" value="PIGGOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1414" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410405-1260-offence-1 t18410405-name-1414"></join>Frederick Piggott</persName> his master; and </rs>
                  <persName id="def2-1260-18410405" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1260-18410405" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1260-18410405" type="surname" value="ALLSHORN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1260-18410405" type="given" value="JAMES EDWARD"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES EDWARD ALLSHORN</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18410405-1260-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410405-1260-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18410405-1260-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>, for feloniously receiving the same, well knowing them to have been stolen; against the Statute, &amp;c.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1416" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1416" type="surname" value="PIGGOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1416" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK PIGGOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an upholsterer, and live in George-street, Richmond. James William Allshorne was living with me as clerk—he came to me in August—on Saturday, the 18th of March, the policeman came and told me he had found some duplicates on my clerk's father, and amongst them one for some printed cotton, and another for some furniture and a looking-glass—he showed me the one for the cotton, which was at a pawnbroker's at Richmond—I went there and identified it—the glass produced is mine, and this is my cotton—one parcel of it was pawned at Richmond; and this is the other part of it—I missed them when I came to examine my stock—James William Allshorn was then living with me—I did not know that he had a father till a few weeks before that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">James William Allshorn. Q.</hi> How do you know that to be your cot<lb></lb>ton? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> By this mark at the back of it, which corresponds with the other piece—I bought two pieces on the 13th of November, and here is the corresponding piece, which has the same mark—I know the glass by a private mark on the back of it, which has been partly erased, but not suf<lb></lb>ficiently—I believe it is your writing.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184104050200"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1417" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1417" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1417" type="surname" value="WYLLIE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1417" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WYLLIE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Edwards, a pawnbroker. This seven yards and a half of cotton were pawned by James Edward Allshorn, the father, on the 23rd of December, in the name of Jones.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1418" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1418" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
